= Grid Cutter =
#context: sop
#type: node

"""Recursively cuts polygons into smaller pieces using axis-aligned cuts."""

== Overview ==

Grid Cutter repeatedly bisects input polygons using axis-aligned cuts. Each iteration selects a cut axis (X or Z) and position based on the Half Ratio parameter.

Works well inside a For-Each Primitive loop to independently cut each piece.

TIP:
    Enable __Auto Align__ when running inside a For-Each Primitive loop so each piece is aligned to the X/Z plane before cutting.

@parameters

Iterations:
    #id: iterations
    Number of cut iterations to perform.

Auto Align (or Cut X/Z Only):
    #id: auto_align
    Aligns each piece to the X/Z plane before cutting. When disabled, all cuts are made in world-space X and Z.

Force Cut Long Side:
    #id: force_cut_long_side
    Always cuts along the longer axis of the bounding box at each iteration.

Half Ratio:
    #id: helf_ratio
    Controls how close each cut is to the midpoint. `0` cuts at the center. `1` allows cuts anywhere along the length.

Global Seed:
    #id: global_seed
    Random seed for cut position variation.

Min Area Limited:
    #id: min_area_limited
    Prevents pieces smaller than __Min Size__ from being cut further.

Min Size:
    #id: min_size
    Minimum piece size. Pieces smaller than this value are not cut.
